text: Pyrausta antisocialis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Munroe in 1976. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from New Mexico and Arizona.mothphotographersgroup Adults are on wing from June to August.Bug Guide ==References== Category:Moths described in 1976 antisocialis Category:Moths of North America
title: Pyrausta antisocialis
